         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511"><!-- p2l6-r15 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Hd1e108">Rubrica 15</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De vulgari seu famosa asseueratione facti</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e114">
              De uulgari seu 
              <lb ed="#B"/>famosa asseueratione facti Rubrica 15
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e121">
              <lb ed="#B"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e117">YSocrates in exortationibus 
              <lb ed="#B"/>capitulo 2</ref> & <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e129">verere crimina tam 
              <lb ed="#B"/>et si falsa sunt nam plerique 
              <lb ed="#B"/>veritatem ignorant opinionem autem 
              <lb ed="#B"/>coniectant</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e137">
              <lb ed="#B"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e136">UIrgilius<!--line jumps up--> eneydos libro 4 circa<!--line jumps down--> princi</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e141">fama malum quo 
              <lb ed="#B"/>non ualde velocius ullum &
              <lb ed="#B"/>Mobilitate uiget uiresque ac<lb ed="#B"/>quirit 
              eundo & praua motu 
              <lb ed="#B"/>primo mox sese attollit in au<lb ed="#B"/>ras
              & Ingrediturque solo: et caput inter nubila 
               condit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e156">
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e154">Li. 7. ante med. et in. 3. et in. 8.</ref>
        <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e158">Fama volat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e164">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e165">Tullius topicorum. c. 4. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e168">Fama vulgi est
        quoddam multitudinis testimonium.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e174">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e177">Quintilianus declam. 17 declam. et finali</ref>
        <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e178">Rumor est res sine teste sine iudice res ex in
        certis: improbissima: maligna: fallax.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e186">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e190">Seneca in prouerb.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e190">Bona opinio hominum
        tutior est pecunia. Bona fama in tenebris
        proprium splendorem obtinet. Damnum appellandum
        est cum mala fama lucrum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e200">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e206">Marcialis cocus li. vndique suscepto. c. 3</ref>
        <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e204">Rumor falsidicus surgit: et ecce cadit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e210">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e217">Auctor libro de formula honeste vite. c. 4</ref>
        <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e214">Rumoribus criminum et suspitionibus 
               minime sis credulus: sed potius malignis qui per
        speciem simplicitatis ad nocendum aliquibus
        surrepunt oppositissimus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e227">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e235">Lucanus li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e231">Innumeras soluit falsa 
               preconia linguas.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e237">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e247">Boetius de consolatione lib. i. c. 12. et pen.</ref>
        <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e241">Plures magnum nomen falsis vulgi opinioni <!--144.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="59-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  bus abstulerunt.
        Sapiens bonum suum non popularim rumore:
        sed conscientie veritate metitur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e260">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e271">Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 7. e. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e264">Nulla
        potestas est que qualitatem fame sue de ore
        hominum possit auferre.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e272">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e285">Auctor rudium dogmatis li. 2</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e276">Error minimo
        crescit: sed non cito fama quiescit.
        Quamuis mentitur crescit eundo tamen.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-d1e284">
               
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Rd1e299">Prouerb. metri. extraordi. li. vag.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d44511-Qd1e288">Fama 
               boni lente: volat inuidia retinente.
        Fama repleta malis: auium deducitur alis.</quote>
            </p>
